-- TPG to Fund GlobeOp Buyout With $291 Million of Debt Financing
-- B y   P a t r i c i a   K u o
-- 2012-02-01T12:02:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/tpg-to-fund-globeop-buyout-with-291-million-of-debt-financing.html
TPG Capital LLP will fund its buyout
of  GlobeOp Financial Services SA (GO/) , a hedge fund administrator,
with $291 million of debt.  Credit Suisse Group AG is arranging the financing,  Fort
Worth , Texas-based TPG said in a statement today.  The private equity firm agreed to buy GlobeOp, based in
 London  and  New York , for about 508 million pounds ($800
million), or 435 pence a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patricia Kuo in London at 
 pkuo2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net  